content: I purchased this game way back when it was on Steam. As soon as I saw that it was available on Android, it struck me how the game would fit perfectly on a mobile phone. I was not disappointed. This game is great, highly recommended for anyone who enjoys a simple puzzle challenge.

I usually find puzzle games to be pretty dull on the app store. This game immediately gripped me, and is keeping my attention longer than than I'd like it to! It's relaxing and simple, yet hard enough for a comfortable challenge.
Fantastic gane, very relaxing
So cool! My 8 year old loves playing this too!
Very enjoyable game, challenging yet simplistic makes you think but also relaxing, no time limits and it doesn't get so difficult to make me want to give up. Love the sound effects as well
Yes! I like it! My brain needs stimulation! This will work! Great job devs!!
Calm and relaxing
Finally we got cloud saving! Thanks for this amazing game.
Superb game. Thanks for implementing cloud save support !
It's fun at first but after a bit, the puzzles don't get any more difficult and there are no new mechanics. At which point you're basically stuck solving the same puzzle over and over and over.

Amazing game! Personally one of my favorite puzzle games and I play it everyday. There are ALOT of levels. I especially love how this game has daily levels. Some games give you levels to play, and once you are done them, the game is over. However, in LYNE daily packs appear giving more of a challenge and sort of making the game "endless". I love the game design and the way it works. 5/5 stars.
Like therapy #soundon

It is an awesome puzzle game. Pros: Cute UI design, Gameplay is so addictive, You need to use your brain, Sometimes relaxing, Many levels, Many colors theme. Cons: Can be boring if you can't finish the level, Need more feature (like cloud save maybe?). 9.2/10 Stars for a great game with style.
wonderful and fun, great little brain teasers and pretty UI
Looks simple but progresses quickky. Great brain exercise, pleasant, no time pressure. I can only do a few levels at a time, then come back to the game in an hour or two. Very enjoyable!
It feels like meditation and algebra all at once, and I love it
i don't often bother with writing reviews on games, but this one is pure brilliance.
Love it! Makes me think about how to connect the dots with each puzzle being different.
awesome game! intuitive and challenging!
Fun and addictive, have it on my pc and phone.
Compelling, relaxing, and well supported. I initially found this for PC on steam and had to buy it when I found it for Android.

It's nice and relaxing. The sound effects are calming and the levels get your brain going so this isn't yet another mindless game. I originally got it back when Starbucks gave away apps and just had to purchase it when I switched to Android. Highly recommend this game to people all the time.
It's good... That's all I got...

Good job! 1st for no ads or in-app purchase, I am always happy to purchase 
quality work. 2nd for the simple yet deceptive challange. If there were 
more than 5 stars I would change my review. Nice work.
This game is AWESOME!! It exercises my brain a lot.

Enjoyable, but quickly becomes repetitive. Puzzles that require you to be economical with the connective resources I enjoyed most. Puzzles that give you an excessive amount of connective resources irritated me. YMMV
Such a great, relaxing, and challenging hallenging game. The sounds and visuals make for a wonderful gaming experience.
Great game.  I wish I could export my progress for when I change phones.  Right now when I change phones, I have to restart the game completely all over.
Great puzzle game, even if (like me) you aren't normally a fan of the genre. The gameplay is intuitive yet complex and the minimalist audio is perfectly suited to the game's aesthetic.

I absolutely love this game. Had it years ago for free but just now bought it. Rare for me to buy apps with this one is worth it. Simple yet complex and I appreciate the minimalist graphics and music.
Literally the best thinking game I have ever come across on Google Play and Steam, splendid work, Thomas!
Love the simplicity of the layout. The puzzles are challenging and offer plenty if varience.
This is a great game! Challenging, simple graphics, beautiful sounds, not as easy as you would think!
I played this game 3 times from A to Z and I still want to come back to it on every new device I get. At night, I often dream that I'm connecting shapes.

The definition of simple to learn with increasing challenge. Concept is simple and works great that makes you think. Plus daily level sets that do NOT require Internet to get! Worth checking out if you like puzzle games that make you think.
This is so cool. As a senior with most of my brain shut down it helps to stimulate my ability to think. Great game.
A wonderful challenge and a fun game.
This game is a good time user. Notice I didn't say waster. It's entertaining and challenging and I feel like the developers have a real gem here.
Simultaneously stimulating and relaxing. A personal favorite.
Not good idea.pls refund my money back to me
This game really suits me. If I have a few minutes to spare I open the game and complete a few levels. I also love the sounds/music, adds a futuristic element!
Love this game. Daily updates always giving new levels, and it gets really challenging later on. Worth the money!
It totally helps me unwind after a long day!
I'm actually sad that I have completed all the levels. Now what should I play? Lyne is the perfect game!
Have you ever emailed the developer?... Well, don't waste your time.
Got this game on steam a while ago, thrilled they have a phone version as well! Didn't hesitate to purchase it and regret nothing, one of my favourite puzzle games.
gorgeous aesthetic...and super addicting
Visuals, sound, interface, game mechanics - all beautiful.
Thoroughly enjoying and engaging, excellent replay and overall value. Still one of my all time favorites!
Perfect game for my puzzle brain! Always challenging, never impossible. Keep up the amazingness! :)
Really solid game- interesting level progression, no IAP and lovely music!
A rare mix of perfect gameplay and perfect aesthetics. Good job!
Love it, nice and simple to learn but fun and relaxing -  would love it as a widget on my home screen though please :)
It's a pain to start over everytime I upgrade my phone or rom.
Bought it on Steam, loved it! Downloaded on phone and tablet. Well done!

Overall nice game. Everyday new content after unlocking. Just did not like the tulip color scheme. Looking forward to unlocking other schemes. Can it be linked with Google account or something? Restoring game advancement is one thing I dearly miss.
This is so great :) high quality

Seriously great, probably the best simple puzzle game on the market right now. Beautiful graphics, well-designed sound and interaction, and a nice difficulty curve. The infinite supply of daily levels is really nice, even though all 26 levels of the main game will still take you ages to get through.
Totally absorbing, well worth the small fee

I love puzzle games but struggle to find ones I like. I love the fact that you give several levels to start with and once you get a level you release all 25 sections for that level. The daily levels are a great mix of easy to extreme. Basically best money I have spent.
If you are reading this, then you should buy this.
This game has hundreds of levels, but also gets new levels every day. This way the game never gets old and is actually worth the money unlike many games.
Great to see an Aussie developer doing well - looking forward to your next game!
Very Enjoyable, the difficulty progression is such to not become ridiculously impossible, very well balanced. Untangles the brain after a hard day
Why is this not more popular? An amazing game
Very chill and relaxing, fun gameplay difficult enough, but not annoyingly brain busting. Also own it on PC.

Once you pop you cannot stop. Intriguing, yet relaxing. Well done.  The above was my review after testing the game out.  Now that I've completed it I have these questions - shouldn't the developers introduce more levels? The points on the game show 243/999.  Will 756 points need to be gained from the daily challenges?  Looks like a bit of an imbalance to me. Would appreciate feedback. Thanks

This is a simple difficult game! Easy to play and get hooked on. Fun and challenging, even the game sounds are intriguing. They make you wonder if you're doing well or they're messing with your head. This game is worth it!
Nice puzzle time waster that actually  requires some thought.

I switched away from the app after finishing set U but before the next set got unlocked, and when I came back the app reloaded, U is finished, and I have no unlocked sets. Is there any way I can unlock V to keep playing?
Despite the fact that there is only 26 levels you can play and then have to wait for the dailies levels to continue, it's an awesome game for any puzzle-lovers
Look & feel of this app is appealing. Very clean & simple. Finding it really tough in later levels but will persevere!
Equal parts satisfying and achingly frustrating
Addictive game in its simplicity and same time challenging.
Great game!

Fantastic puzzle game with a steady difficulty curve. Weirdly, I found it harder to play if I stopped and over-thought any path. If I were to criticise this game, I would say it is a little too trial-and-error and made easier if you 'just go' and let your subconscious do all the work. I wouldn't call this a negative as other classic puzzle games like tetris are beaten in the same way.  That said, I absolutely loved this game . Very  pick-up-and-play and time flies by when you get into it.
Beautifully designed, very addictive and no pay to win nonsense!
Needs ambient music
Nice
This game is simply challenging and fun. Clean and simple.
Simple and elegant puzzle game. Get it.
Really cute and simple design, really nicely executed.

and finally got it a couple weeks ago.  I didn't like it at first; the gameplay starts out simply and I didn't know if it would get better.  However, on a different night, I kept playing and it DEFINITELY gives a challenge.  Starting on set V, some puzzles take what feels like infinite tries, but the frustration is not like with other games.  I love this game now.  My one small complaint is that there is no good information about various aspects, and I am left confused about what I call the "red screen" from the start menu that starts with "???."  I can't stand long and boring tutorials, but wish for just basic instructions in text when I have a question.
Great game, more than worth the purchase. And on top of that there is no ads and no IAP pushing whatsoever. Just a great original game and nothing else.
Was this written in html5? *update* loading times seem to have improved.
replyContent: Hi Erik, the new update should address the loading times. It was built using Unity.

content: This is a really fun and challenging puzzle/pattern game. Its simplistic design and easy interaction make it the perfect game to play from waiting in an office to killing time on your friend's couch. I've just beaten all levels through Set Z and enjoy the daily challenges that come afterward. Highly recommended.

A puzzle game that is easy to learn but a challenge  to master, if you think you can.  Gets you old gears crunching while helping you enter an almost ZEN like state of mind.  An excellent game and a bit puzzling.   (:
Relaxing and simultaneously engaging. Great game!
Keeps my mind thinking in terms of path recognition.
ENJOYING IT A LOT SO FAR.
Best app I've bought in a while!
No ads. No in app purchases. Just thinking puzzles about constraint solving.

Good thinker game; you develop a sense for patterns and strategies that help you advance. Would be five stars but after beating the game (25 puzzles in 26 world's...) you have to wait each day to get new ones... may uninstall and reinstall just to play them all again but there's some system of collecting triangles that get you some undisclosed prize... just buy it.
Great creative work from the developer. Too bad people are trying to rip off his ideas...

I love this game. It's even better that there are no in app purchases or ads. The only thing I would ask for would be Google Play integration, with achievements and such, but otherwise a very polished experience.
the fact that the app starts up so slowly and then also has the player go through several menus before you can finally start the next level is a tiny bit frustrating.
Excellent
Simple rules, complex ways to fit them together, effortless navigation and a nice minimalist interface.
Good thinking game. Simple concept but requires some thought.
Awesome is the only way I can describe this game, if you like this kind of game that is.
Simply brilliant
Simple and endlessly enjoyable!
Simple Fun
Where entertainment, simplicity and cognitive exercise meets!
So good
Loads of levels to keep you playing along with a set of daily legless that change every day.
It's a really neat game. Just, it gets rather boring after a short time, since the author had only one major idea, and he didn't do much more than implementing that one.

Lyne is a great game that is easy to learn, but can be extremely challenging. The daily level sets combined with the large catalog of standard levels is a great way for this clean and elegant game to stay fresh with the same familiar assets and rules. This is easily worth the purchase price, if not more. Keep up the amazing work.

Just a simple puzzle game!  And they don't want blood as a term of service,  nor your first born with permission! No trying to sneak in friend invites,  and no cheating you on lives so they can ask for your money.  It's a relaxed atmosphere,  but addictive fun.
Puzzles present a great variety of challenge to keep you engaged.

There are a few error when dragging the line over a longer range. Adding to play games achievements would be nice. Different backgrounds and colour themes would also be a good addition. Other then that, the game is good, but then it is simple enough. It does get repetitive after a while.

In an ecosystem filled with glossy buttons and over-the-top characters, the minimal graphics and sounds in this game make it even more of a treat to overcome each challenge. The premise is easy to understand in seconds, and the difficulty of its puzzles ramps up nicely. A great game that everyone should try at least once.
I own this on PC and bought it as soon as I knew it was on a Android. I am very pleased that it has all the features of the PC version (daily levels and pallets) and I was happy to purchase it.

I like the elegant interface. Easy to learn yet sometimes tricky to finish. Will keep you entertained for hours if you enjoy puzzle games. Only small adjustment (beyond "more levels") I'd like to see is having the alphabet order reversed so that the most recently unlocked levels are always on top. Slightly annoying and needless to always scroll down. Oh and the "secret menu" requires me to open my browser? I don't like opening mystery links. Fun idea but not practical.
currently downloading, will update this review after giving it a proper go. based on the screenshots and art direction i'm loving it already.
Brilliant

In my top ten games.  Have more hours on this game than all the quells and candy crush.  Wonderful game. Plus there are daily games, so if you finish the game (if you finish, I'm on W) you can still play.

Its a wonder that this game doesn't have more downloads. Anyone who enjoys puzzle games needs this. I haven't showed a soul this game who hasn't become instantly addicted. Keep making games like this, and I'll keep buying them.
This game is very minimalistic, and pretty entertaining at the same time. I recommend everyone at least give it a shot, but some may not like it because of its simplicity.
Striking aesthetically and some nice simple but engaging puzzle gameplay
A minimalist, artistic and hypnotic  puzzle experience.
A gentle and tricky puzzler to exercise the deeper parts of the hidden mind. It may seem to begin simple but don't worry, it will get tricky and boggling fairly quickly. Love the design and sound.
Can keep you fascinated for hours. Keeps track of your puzzle and it keeps  getting harder and harder have it on cellphone and tablets.
A very simple yet completely intricate title. Easy to play and hard to master.
Starts out easy and intelligently escalates the difficulty....the daily puzzles are nice.... :) Wish it had cloud save though.... :-/
And suprisingly addictive.
Loved it
Fantastic game. With new puzzles daily the value in this game never stops. I wish there were more unlockable skins, just to have something to aim for.
Add Google games support and save progress
Quick and satisfying.
So awesome!
Really enjoy this game. One thing that I really hope from it is adding support for Google Play Game service and being able to save my game on the cloud.
Elegance

Still playing through the prebuilt levels, but it's certainly worth your time and money. It nicely fills the void in my app life left when I beat tapes, a conceptually similar game. It solves the main problem I had with tapes, which is that it was too short!
Being colourblind, it's incredibly rare to find a puzzle game that I can truly enjoy. This game is fun, challenging, rewarding and very accessible.

Exactly the kind of puzzle game to distract my mind for a couple minutes here and there without requiring a commitment. Daily games keep new content coming. I make it an extra challenge to complete a level before the chime fades out.

Great simple concept with complexity and challenging puzzles, style and execution. Really zen art and sound with unlockable color palettes. And 25-50 Daily puzzles with escalating difficulty throughout the week, all for one price.

This game was exactly what I was hoping it would be.  Very well balanced, it feels like I'm having to think, but I'm never actually stumped.  It's hard to put down, and well worth the 2.50 I paid for it.
Fun and relaxing
Just the thing to do for a few minutes in the morning as I wake up. Innovative game.  No pop ups or flashy things.  Smooth game play. Lots of daily freebies.
If you play one level you want to play more. It is simple, difficult and a lot of fun
A very simple to play, very addictive game this. Connect the same colored shapes without crossing the other connections. If it sounds boring, it is not. A great little game this.
Loved it on pc (Steam) and now I can take it with me!
Sounds, graphics, touch response, intuitive, thoughtful, relaxing, engaging, colour coordination...love itüëç Only one update suggestion...just a few more varieties of sound effects üòÜ Thanks!
Play this game everyday

Great graphics and gameplay. Love the feel of the game. I enjoyed it on PC; love it even more on my tablet. Glad they kept daily puzzle sets in this version! 5 stars! My only concern: what is this "Unlocked ???" all about!?
This app is great. I use it to keep my mind alert and I also let my granddaughter play it to develop her reasoning skills.
Beautiful UI, a wealth of puzzles ranging in difficulty. Love that there are daily levels. Great game when you have a few minutes to work your brain.
I got this for Steam first, and figure it'd make a great Android game. Low and behold, it's know the market. I had to pick it up and it certainly doesn't disappoint. Great job!
...it may cause me to miss my flights while waiting to board.
I bought the mobile version after the steam version, because I can't stop playing it. <3
Novel gameplay concept, soothing background music, and non-intrusive permissions make this one a winner in my book.
Very well crafted.
Various heuritics are working on the game, like take the shortests paths and repair, which makes the game interesting, but maybe sometimes too easy.

Lyne has a beautiful presentation, very clean. Excellent and classy sound effects. FANTASTIC interface!! A+ for that.  The game play itself is interesting and a new idea to me. I would say that it's getting easier as it goes along though. Paradoxically, the more elements in the puzzle, the more daunting it looks, but the easier it is. You can finish many of the puzzles from level C onwards in one attempt, within a minute or two. It stops being a real challenge, and is now more of a task to complete.  Maybe as it goes on, it will introduce new types of elements, which will ramp up the challenge and interest.
The gameplay and idea is quite smooth. However, after a while it gets repetitive and there is nothing new to offer. I am at level k and reluctant to play any more. It was fun while it lasted.
good

I had been eyeing this game for a while, but was never sure whether or not to actually shell out the money, as little as it is. As soon as I did though, I got hooked on the simple game play, the ambient noises, and the amazing color palettes. It seems like an endless game, completely worth the money as I will be playing this for a very long time.
Excellent, unique game! Thank you, Thomas.
If you like spatial puzzles, this is the stunningly designed game for you! No stress, just fun.

I'm so glad they put daily sets in the game so if I just want to feel accomplished I can play 1 to 3 star difficulty levels. I would put progressively better themes to unlock though. I think the blue and gold is better than the next duller one ahead. But over all a perfect little game!
A great, thought consuming game. Elegant.

A very nicely designed game. Simple and effective graphics, and atmospheric sound.  Simple to pick up and challenging at the same time as the difficulty ramps up. Puzzles are fairly short so I'm finding myself playing it during short breaks and intervals. Well worth the price.
Relaxing. Great game to play when you're bored.
Evolves in difficulty smoothly with no surprises.  Can be challenging, but just enough to keep you playing without being frustrating.

A simple concept that gets more complex as you go, but without a time limit you don't feel rushed.  I just bought it and have already open a couple of level sets and the daily puzzles. A easy game to play a little or I could see playing hours.  And unlike many games no in app purchases running up the price.

Lyne is a great puzzle game with a nice design and an easy-to-use interface. I bought this game several weeks ago and I have yet to finish all the puzzles, so for a small price, you get a game that will keep you entertained for quite some time.
Wonderful game!
Amongst the best.
Great game to pass time and keep your brain working. The very simple and clean look hides a very complex and addictive game. 5 stars!

I cannot imagine a way to improve this app. The puzzle concept is solid, similar to some existing games yet still fresh. The visuals are exquisite, beautiful without any frills or excess information. The sequence after you complete a level, which has your solution glow white, is surprisingly satisfying, letting you look at the structure in a different way. The sounds played are soothing and seem natural. Beyond all this, the procedurally generated levels (with built-in difficulty rating) and color pallete unlock system keep the game fresh beyond the already extensive set of included levels. Here's hoping for more from this developer!
Enjoyed this puzzle game very much.   Great!
Nippy graphics, works smooth and flawless. Well thought out graduating from easy to really challenging.
I take it all back
This game is simultaneously challenging and entertaining. Exactly the kind of game I need!
Enjoying the challenge.
It's clean, deceptively simple, and thoroughly enjoyable. Lots of replay value. I highly recommend this.
Simple yet beautiful  game!
This is a great game, it's easy to play and challenging to master. Download at your own risk, it is guaranteed to shorten your life. I cannot recommend this game more, 5 stars does not do it justice.

Unlike some other apps this one is actually fun and relaxing. Games challenge the mind but. Don't overwhelm the eyes. Best part is they don't have a bunch of cheats they try to sell you like candy crush.
This game along with Strata and Kami is all you need on your droid.
Challenging
It'd be nice to see immersion for 4.4 back
Simple, elegant and fiendishly challenging.  Everything you want in a puzzle game.
Every day I look forward to the daily puzzles. Now I just wish there were more achievements after reaching 200. :)
Exactly what I was looking for in a mobile game. Clean, simple, and hard to put down.
Well chilled, nice little puzzler. The complete opposite of candy crush, and I mean that as a compliment!

Only game I've found that I categorically enjoy playing. It's beautiful,  challenging,  just the right level of maddening on . occasion- and I love the random victory chimes. I keep searching for others "like this" but haven't found anything close.  Please keep the daily sets coming !!
I love how it's extremely entertaining, and easy to learn how to play. I have not experienced any bugs or the game closing on me. It's very well developed.

I thought the game was a good mental challenge and showed it to a 9yo cousin, he steamed through the levels. My 3yo got interested and with only a little assistance got to level A18, then needed more help to complete the rest of the A levels.  I was surprised at how well the kids took to the game. Very intuitive. A win for all ages.
I completed all 10x25 puzzles and am now waiting for next day's auto‚Äìgenerated puzzles...
Great game - simple, abstract, difficult at times, each puzzle can be solved in from one minute to many hours.
Simple and fun. Very easy to pick up yet very interesting. Great job!
Great puzzle game. Simple and minimal but pleasing graphics and sound.
Fun simple but challenging
Really clean, well designed, and implemented. Minor nit would be more "clever" levels that have less of a machine touch and more human creativity in level design.
Clean, minimal, addictive
Challenging
I wish more mobile games were like this.  The style is understated and well executed, nothing is popping up telling you to rate or buy. Just smooth clean puzzle solving.
Relaxing and challenging in equal measure. You can go into a trance playing this as you gently connect up the points. Highly recommended.
Simple yet elegant.
Simple, fun, nice looking
In 4.4 the whole screen was used in the previous version but now it leaves the black navigation bar there, I liked the full screen! Bring it back!

Fun! Simple but satisfying idea for a puzzle game. Not very challenging, though. The difficulty is very inconsistent, and even many of the "advanced" levels are quite boring when you play logically. Some are much better and require some real reasoning, but those are few and far between.
This is one of the coolest puzzle games I've ever played. Thanks for a great game.
a very good puzzle game.
I have never seen this type of puzzle before, and the presentation is flawless.
... With my phones battery life now that I've started playing this game.

Exactly what I want in a mobile game. It's usually something I play while watching TV or listening to a podcast/audio book, but some of the harder puzzles require my full attention! I make sure to check out the daily puzzles regularly, even on the easy days. They're still incredibly satisfying to solve. Something about the motion and sound effects involved.
Great time killer
Nice and simple gameplay, hugely frustrating after not very long üò∂
Really simple and meditative
Nothing too taxing, but challenging enough, and with the daily levels too this game is a beautiful bargain
Great game to get your brain working without needing to rush
Really laid back and relaxing. Great sound effects and nice slick visual feel.
Perfect
Simple and elegant but addictive.  Want more levels!

Have to say I don't do reviews on games but this has got my attention. Simple easy to pick up and hard to put down. I love puzzle games that make you think out side the box and this is one thumbs up from me

Really worth the money. A fantastic app with a simple yet addictive puzzle based format and a beautiful art style. By far my favourite app of 2014 so far. I play it on the bus and around the house it is great to play seriously and just casually and I have reached the point when I just find myself reaching for my phone and opening up lyne.
Good graphics and animation coupled with a pleasing control scheme. Proper puzzle game give it a go.
Good way to keep you brain working while on the bus, waiting for someone, etc.
Yet addictive

Basic design theme and elements are used throughout to great effect and it's honestly more fun than I had passed initial judgement on from the example video. Glad I took a chance and purchased it. For a puzzle game, it has it's own unique charm.

Very addictive, UI is elegant, clean, smooth, similar to the popular Flow game, but much better. No ads too! If I didn't have to be up in 6 hours for a big day at World Vision, I would be playing still. Hahhaha. Thought I would take a moment and add this review. Spent only about 30 minutes in the game. Easy ***** I don't have many games on phone, this one is worth keeping on for sure! Worth the $2.50. Thank you! Rooted - SlimKat GS4.
Would be 5 stars if the app used Google Play games services to sync progression b/t devices.
Great thinking game!

Played this game on an iPad before downloading on my Droid phone.   Very fun game, but for some reason has no idea which way my phone is oriented. On my phone, it flips the window around spastically to the point that the game is impossible to play.
One of the best puzzle games that I have ever played. Challenging and relaxing at the same time. A must for puzzle enthusiasts!
Easy to understand, challenging to master.  Love it.
A great way to relax

This game is what I call perfection! Its simple, beautiful and well done! The atmosphere created by the graphics and sounds(especially this) is so relaxing!!! And the game is challenging but not at the point of getting frustrating, the difficulty is just right! Truly a master piece of the puzzles!
This would benefit from a leaderboard and integration with the Google Play Games API
Didn't expect it to be this flawless.

This is my favorite puzzle game on android for me. My one request is to integrate Google play games. It can be anything! Come up with achievements when you pass certain points in the game and leaderboards.
The game colors and graphics soothes ones eyes and mind to the extent you get yourself immersed inside its world. Plz bring forth future updates soon.

I really enjoy how this game can seem to make me think for a while on some levels while not actually frustrating me. Something about the gameplay somehow helps me to relax. Definitely worth the price for it.
If you value your productivity, do not play.
The best game yet. First time I've given 5 stars to a game. Absolutely elegant!
replyContent: Haha, sorry this just made me laugh because you gave it 3 stars.

content: This game is just PERFECT. It is beautiful, relaxing, easy, but not too much. And NO ads so far! Love it
Pleasing feel, the puzzles are wonderfully crafted. Simple, almost zenlike to play, but not dead easy; this game takes thought. Refreshing, thank you!
replyContent: Thanks Sarah! Looking forward to more Northway games. (if this is the Sarah Northway I'm thinking of) :).

content: This game ranges from simple to very complex and never seems to get boring.  Recommended!

Not the most original puzzle game in th world, but out of the many similar games, this one is doing something right. It's also visually pleasent. Has lots of levels, and till now I haven't "cracked" the best method to approach it like I usually do in most of the games. One of the best of its kind.
Best puzzle game I've ever played, and probably the first one I've ever liked enough to finish. Its bugging me though, what is that ??? Menu thing that I unlocked??????
Really cool game! Challenging, relaxing, but starts to feel monotonous after a bit. Wish there were more to it sometimes.

This is an excellent puzzle game. Better than the flow games by far. The sound is soothing, and the puzzles are challenging without being unbearably frustrating. I enjoy unlocking color palettes, and the daily levels offer endless playability. The only things that would make it better are the ability to unlock new sound themes, other visual themes (maybe different shapes), and the ability to earn hints (or use the in-game "triangle currency" ) to purchase them.

Some of the puzzles are very tricky. I love that there isn't a time limit. There are many levels and daily updates. Great game! Although I wish you could create profiles so you don't have too start all over on a new device.
Casual gaming at its best.   Simple,  mesmerizing and seemingly endless.
Addicting and fun
Can hear the synapses twanging in my head..
Difficult to put down. As the puzzles become more complex it is more maddening,  yet the overall experience is relaxing.

Puzzle lovers unite! This is a truly wonderful game which can tantalize you with it simple to extremely complex puzzles. Aesthetically stunning, with level sets added daily, this is one app that the fun never ends. Developers, I thank you, amazing work.
If you love puzzle games, you'll spend a lot of enjoyable time with this one.
Loving the daily generated levels...
Well design. Well thought out. Executed perfectly. I don't usually pay for games. This one was worth it.
Game.... I was skeptical at first, but very addictive and smooth.
very inventive and clever!
Best puzzle game out there but needs more levels. Beat all of the packs so far
Excellent
Lovely looking game. Difficult enough to keep you interested, but not too hard that you just want to give up.
Take my money

Only thing,  is there a way to finish stage H14?  I beat all other levels but that one,  to me is impossible. Maybe add a social part to game like puzzle retreat.  Either that or give hints,  since I'm stumped.
Brilliant game, great thinking puzzle
....and very addictive.  Just wish there were more puzzles available.
This game is amazingly well done. It's difficult, but not so much that it is frustrating. There are new levels every day, so you will never be finished.
And that is something all husbands will relate to
Very pleasant game indeed. Daily puzzles are added bonus. Would be great to have more unlockable stuff to gain a more exciting sense of progress. But the game itself I like very much indeed.

Awesome game I caught it being reviewed on All About Android.  Love how the colour pallette, basic shapes and simple rules foster a seemingly elementary game play.  It all works together for a Zen like experience.  Well as as Zen as I'm likely to get.  The sound and accompanying vibration feed back are a nice touch too, though some who don't like electronic music or sounds may be put off.

Simple concept, flawless execution. Daily puzzles keep it fresh. Plenty of puzzles included from the beginning. Unlocks are good. Amazingly simple but endlessly enjoyable. Absolutely worth the asking price.
Relaxing and challenging without being frustrating.
Food for the mind
I bought this game over a week ago and have barely been able to put it down since.
Bought this game to replace Tetris (after 10+ years as my go-to app for killing time). It does not disapoint.  It's easy to learn, fun, and has a very zen-like quality that I find very relaxing.

The game looks great and the daily levels alone are enough to keep me hooked.   This is a game for both casual and hardcore puzzle lovers. If you love puzzles, buy this game. It's a must have, and especially for a Mobile game.
With daily free dlc on top
One of the best puzzle games I've ever played. Relaxing and difficult, but never exceedingly so. Graphics and sound are gorgeous, and number of level is virtually endless.

This game is a great way to pass the time. Some levels are complex enough that you have to actually work at it for a bit, but not so frustratingly difficult that you want to throw your phone against the wall.
This game is incredible. It's really simple but really challenging, but never too hard. Definitely worth the 2.50 price, probably more.

Its simple to get started and the difficulty ramps up at the perfect rate. The awesome thing about this game is how you are never stuck for too long. I think it is a good balance of difficulty and simplicity.
it would be nice if you could add s pen compatibility

This app is a great way to unwind while still stimulating your brain... Definitely worth it!  Edit: the app decided that it was not, in fact installed, and upon my uninstalling it and then reinstalling it, I noted that my progress was lost... Kind of an annoying bug, hence the list of a star!
replyContent: So sorry this has happened! I hope it wasn't something I have done to cause it. If you would like to get the first 20 Trytes enter NNYYLLEE in the main menu, a sound will confirm correct entry. Thanks for the review.

content: I would LOVE for you to add the API to play from the same level across different devices. Otherwise, the gameplay is brilliant and worth a download.

Great puzzle game, gets your brain working spatially. Nicely presented, the sound helps to develop a rhythm to play. The feedback when you have made an error is intuitive and makes finding a solution easier. Finally, the first few tutorial levels are very well set so there's absolutely no reason for text instructions. Recommended!
It is simple yet amazing puzzle game. Sometimes it can be frustrating but it is addictive. Good job :)
Simple, elegant, beautiful, challenging, instantly addictive. One of the best games I've ever played.
Very sleek and fun to play.
Great design, great game play, great sound effects.

No frills, no unnecessarily long tutorial, just a fantastic puzzle game through and through.  After the first puzzle, you already have "how to play" down - and it's just a single line! - and before long you're bouncing your way between the points like a pro.  Also great to see that there isn't any   rating screen after every puzzle, something which can easily take up the majority of your playtime instead of the actual puzzles.  I'll certainly be looking forward to anything else you release in the future!
Intuitive, logic, fun

Beautifully simple and gorgeously minimalist. I couldn't image a better app to fill in the gaps in my day. In either quick bursts or serious binges Lyne never fails to entertain. It takes the formula from apps like flow free and improves upon them infinitely with addicting game play and an art style that can't be beat.
The puzzles are engaging and challenging without being frustrating. The design is gorgeous and makes me want to continue playing even more.
I enjoyed the Linux version and this is even better with touch control
A deceptively simple puzzle game that frustrates whilst somehow being entertaining.

The gameplay is simple yet the further you go the puzzles do get more difficult. The UI is flawless and very pretty. The only gripe I would have would be the music. I wish there were a couple of more tracks. It tends to become too monotonous after a while and I usually have to mute it. Again , this is my personal opinion . I've read a bunch of reviews where people loved the music. All I'm saying is to add a few tracks if possible.
My only wish is that the emersive mode was optional. I like to be able to see the time and battery life and any notifications when playing games like this and I'm not sure it needs to be full screen.
Only three sets in, and it keeps getting inventive and puzzling. Even better, constant updates, today free, and No ads. You're the man, dev
Love it!

This is a deceptively simple, brilliant game, I am easily going to lose hours on this. If you could add save game sync so I can play on my phone and pick up at the same place on my tablet, I would easily up to 5 stars!

I see this as a game and so much more! Due to no time limits, no pressure! The sound effects are relaxing. This is a great challenge for your mind/brain activity! It is actually calming. As the levels increase still no pressure. Especially for those who are forward thinkers with ability to see 2/4/6 lines back also! I am a person who ruminates. None of that here! The creator/staff really READ the comments and are right on fixes/suggestions! Play,Relax and have Fun! How about my Seahawks! Signed Twelve!

Easily one of the best puzzle games ive ever played. Its so simple to grasp but so complex to master. The levels are hard but not impossible and with an almost endless amount of levels to solve I feel Lyne will be a game that will keep me busy for many hours to come.
Very well made design. Great sounds. Wouldn't hurt to add more elements to the puzzles. The difficulty can only be sustained so long.
Fantastically frustrating a true new puzzle idea.  As an electronics engineer it panders to my circuit design brain. Superb value for money. Can't wait to get to the daily challenges.
I really like the layout of this game. It offers considerable challenges without making me grind my teeth. Might replace flow as my relaxing puzzle game.

This game is beautiful and simple. It guides you through the tutorial stages with few words, allowing you to figure out the game and your way of playing it for yourself. It's also been created and executed flawlessly, every touch, drag and swipe does exactly what you expect.  The difficulty also increases at a reasonable rate, and the puzzle at hand never feels frustrating.  I would highly recommend this game for it's relaxing, puzzle solving atmosphere and the developers honesty. No extra payments, just buy the app and play.
Super fun and addictive!
I really enjoy this app. I bought it after seeing its simple design and engaging gameplay in the trailer.
Great puzzler, tests the limits of both human creativity and ingenuity.
Totally addictive.
Simple, sleek, elegant and utterly absorbing. Fantastic little game that you'll easily lose hours of your life to.
It becomes a challenge after a little bit. I have only played the first 2 sets so can not comment on if it's worth the money. The game is good if you like puzzles
Awesome ambience, palette and above all, gameplay.
Fun and casual
Simple. Beautiful. Challenging. Such a great concept. Perfect execution.
So refreshing to find a game that doesn't rely on speed and simulated violence. Relaxing.
Good game, easy yet challenging

This is really good game. Simple concept but solutions become really challenging. I have been stumped a few times. (might have to include solutions for people like me heh)  I'm looking forward to updates and possibilities for this game. Very well done. I'm using a Galaxy Note 3.
I love the style of this game and the pace of increasing challenge. In the early stages, you're learning about the controls, but before you know it you're solving really complex puzzles.
Great design and challenging puzzles.  Difficulty varies with each puzzle and some will be really easy.  Other puzzles for me haven't been so easy but that's a good thing, right?
Good UI, good challenge, continual updates, suitable for short and long sessions etc. All the things a mobile game should have.
So freakin' amazing.
Honestly one of the best games I've played on Android, if not THE best. Easy to learn, I'm always eager to best the next challenge. Keep up the good work!

Very simple design, but beautiful at the same time. Shuttle sounds make it rather relaxing even when it's making you think "what, how, can I do that, that's impossible, oh wait, nope still can't do it" great little game!
No problems other than addiction.
The game is very well designed, has calming sounds, and is good at its intended use. However the loading time is a tad long

I love board puzzle games, this one is everything I like the most in them: simple, challenging and a high replayable value. I'm not even worried about ending the game, with the daily generated puzzles it goes on forever!
Puzzles are challenging without being frustrating. I like that I can jump around to any puzzle that is in an unlocked set. Also love the daily puzzle sets.
It doesn't work on Xperia Play and I can't get a refund. Please add support.
replyContent: Hi Griffin, could you possibly give me any more information? What exactly does not work on your device? This is a touch screen game so there is no use for the buttons on Xperia Play devices. Thanks.

content: I think more could have been done with the sound, but still a good game.
Great design. Clean. Difficulty curve is about right. Clever use of harmonies in sound. Unlocked a colour palette which was my only complaint!
Just love it so simple yet it gets so hard lyne is a simple path building game that can challenge the most ardent puzzler.
Beautiful
Good for if you'd like to stretch your brain in a relaxing way for a minute or two.
This is a nice relaxing game that makes your mind work but us not too difficult.
Well made app, looks great. Great puzzles and endless fun. Well worth it!
Simple yet fun
Simple, good
Samsung S3
Great app very addictive  puzzles!!
A beautiful, intuitive and intriguing game
LYNE has similar game mechanics as the popular Flow, but improves on them in new and interesting ways. One of the few games to look just as good on Android as it does on iOS.
Beautiful - Visually, Audibly, and Mechanically. Thank you, Thomas, for this game.
Because this game is sexay. Go get him girls
